    <main>
        <h1>LeetCode 3761: Maximum Difference Between Adjacent Elements in a Circular Array (C++)</h1>

        <div class="problem-description">
            <p><strong>Problem:</strong>
                You are given a circular array nums. A circular array means that the element after the last element is the first element of the array. For each element in the array, find the maximum absolute difference between the element and its adjacent elements. Return the maximum value among all these differences.
            </p>
            <p><strong>Example:</strong>
                Input: nums = [1,2,4,8,16]<br/>
                Output: 12<br/>
                Explanation: The differences are: |1 - 16| = 15 (circular), |2 - 1| = 1, |4 - 2| = 2, |8 - 4| = 4, |16 - 8| = 8. The maximum is 15.<br/><br/>
                Input: nums = [5,3,2,4]<br/>
                Output: 2<br/>
                Explanation: All adjacent differences are at most 2.<br/><br/>
                Input: nums = [10]<br/>
                Output: 0<br/>
                Explanation: Single element has no adjacent differences.
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="code-container">
            <button class="copy-button" onclick="copyCode(this)">Copy Code</button>
            <pre><code class="language-cpp">class Solution {
public:
    int maxAdjacentDistance(vector&lt;int&gt;&amp; nums) {
        int n = nums.size();
        if (n == 1) return 0;
        
        int maxDiff = 0;
        
        for (int i = 0; i &lt; n; i++) {
            int next = (i + 1) % n;
            maxDiff = max(maxDiff, abs(nums[i] - nums[next]));
        }
        
        return maxDiff;
    }
};</code></pre>
